INSERT INTO message (id, channelId, userId, message, createdAt, updatedAt) VALUES ('1186807818687365201', '1178822630225227818', '239115000424169484', 'Ok while im still in its infancy turso seems to handle the replica synchronization very nicely. I start up the API server and it syncs the live to the replica. \n\nHowever to test the live sync i kept the server running and manually changed the values in some of my tables. When i ran the same api endpoint the replicated database automatically synced with the main database and sent me an updated response. \n\nTLDR: Turso seems to automatically sync the live database with the replica whenever an api call is made meaning our data ""should"" always be up to date. We may run into problems inthe future with massive datasets, however we can combat this by manually syncing the database before heavy api calls.', 1703027433798, 1703027433798);
